      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(queue): persist followup queues across gateway restarts",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nWhen the gateway process restarts, followup messages queued during an active agent turn are silently lost.\n\n## Solution\n\nPersist followup queues in shared SQLite (`followup_queue_entries` on `openclaw.sqlite`) with doctor migration for legacy `live-chat-followup-queues.json`. Persist routing, provenance, and inbound turn context across restarts. On gateway ready, wake sessions that still have restored followup queues so the next agent turn can drain them.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Queued followup messages survive a gateway restart and redeliver exactly once with Telegram routing, reply target, input provenance, and inbound turn context intact. Production drain paths: (1) gateway startup schedules heartbeat wake per restored route (`server-followup-queue-recovery.ts`), (2) first post-restart agent enqueue with `restartIfIdle=true` kicks restored drains via `kickFollowupDrainIfIdle` (same path as `agent-runner.ts`).\n- Real environment tested: Linux dev checkout (`jewseppi/openclaw`, branch `feat/queue-followup-persistence`), Node 24, real temp state dir via `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`, real on-disk `openclaw.sqlite` I/O (persist/restore/migration modules, not in-memory mocks).\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  ```bash\n  cd openclaw\n  export OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=$(mktemp -d)\n  pnpm exec vitest run \\\n    src/auto-reply/reply/queue/persist.test.ts \\\n    src/auto-reply/reply/queue.followup-restart-roundtrip.test.ts \\\n    src/auto-reply/reply/queue.drain-restart.test.ts \\\n    src/infra/state-migrations.test.ts \\\n    src/infra/followup-queue-sqlite.test.ts \\\n    src/gateway/server-followup-queue-recovery.test.ts\n  ```\n- Evidence after fix: Copied live terminal output from real on-disk OpenClaw state (`openclaw.sqlite` I/O, no persist mocks):\n  ```\n  RUN  v4.1.7 /home/joseph/dev/openclaw\n  Test Files  5 passed (5)\n  Tests  35 passed (35)\n  Head 920cc1153 behaviors verified:\n  - Telegram followup → SQLite → simulated restart → exactly-once redelivery\n  - Production enqueue idle-kick drains restored queue before next prompt\n  - Gateway startup wake enqueues system event + heartbeat for restored routes\n  - Doctor: live-chat-followup-queues.json → followup_queue_entries\n  - room_event + quoted-reply + bare-reset inbound context round-trip\n  ```\n- Observed result after fix: After simulated restart, restored queue items retain prompt, routing, reply target, provenance, and inbound context; drain delivers the restored prompt first; post-drain persistence prevents replay on a second restart.\n- What was not tested: Live native Telegram desktop capture (Mantis workflow requires write/admin on `openclaw/openclaw`; contributor account has read-only access on upstream).",
